commentary: McBrine to Rahmat Shah, OUT big turn into him and Rahmat has been given out leg before here. Was it going down? At best that is a marginal call. He's on the back foot as this rips in a long way and beats him on the back foot flick. Strikes him at a leg stump line. Umpire thinks that's hitting leg. It just turned so much. Perhaps his decision to be on the back foot has cost him

commentary: Rankin to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs dropped! And a run-out chance missed! Is that the sign he's destined for this hundred?! Terrible from Ireland. Short of a length ball at off stump, looks to pull it and gets a top edge that lobs up for McBrine at point. He is nowhere near being underneath that by the end. Lunging to his left as he drops it and then throwing at the striker's end. Where there's no one to receive the throw.

commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Dockrell, OUT stumping chance sent upstairs. This could be tight. Dockrell stepped out and didn't get to the pitch of this ball spinning into him. He got body on it, but it richochets off the pad and floats up for Shahzad who takes the bails off as Dockrell stretches back for the crease...and he catches him short! That's the breakthrough! Nabi strikes with his last ball and the partnership is cut short at 143. A superb hand from Dockrell, and a tame end, if not unlucky. He's done his part, but so has Nabi with that last ball
